Gnathosoma
(
Fig. 3
). Five segmented palp 390 long with palpal tibiotarsus nearly strait, apically slightly curved. Palp with gently punctate surface and bare tibiotarsus. Palpal chaetotaxy as follows: trochanter - 0, basifemur - 1 dorsomedial simple seta; telofemur inner surface with 1 medial apophysis, ventrally with stout spinelike seta, anteriorly with 1 spinelike seta; genu with 1 simple seta ventrally, inner surface with 1 spinelike seta, apically with 1 elongate apophysis, outer surface ventrally with 1 simple seta, dorsally with 1 spinelike seta, palpgenual apophysis five times long as adjacent spinelike seta; tibiotarsus inner surface with 1 long simple seta and medially with 1 stout spinelike seta; outer surface with 1 ventrolateral and 1 dorsolateral simple seta; terminating with 1 solenidion (sensu
Den Heyer 2006
) and a small short claw.

Etymology: The name of species (
cyaneus
) is derivated from blueish body colour of living mite.
